# Environment Variables Template
#
# SECURITY WARNING: Never commit files with real values (.env.local, .env.production, etc.)
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values
#
# For production builds, create .env.production with your production values
# For GitHub Actions CI/CD, use GitHub Secrets (see README.md)

# ============================================
# EmailJS - Contact Form (Active)
# ============================================
# REQUIRED: Create account at https://www.emailjs.com
# 1. Add an email service (Gmail, SendGrid, etc.)
# 2. Create template with variables: from_name, from_email, subject, message, to_email, phone, company_name, company_id
# 3. IMPORTANT: In template, set "To Email" to {{to_email}} (required - 422 error if missing)
# 4. Optional: VITE_EMAILJS_TO_EMAIL overrides default recipient (joaomaia@jmsit.cloud)
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id
# VITE_EMAILJS_TO_EMAIL=joaomaia@jmsit.cloud

